One thing I never expected to learn is how human the 121 cockpit is, through all the normalized procedures. The SOPM will not always contain black and white answers to everything. Experience and decisions come into play. Pilots can still have an off day. Startle effect is real. Boredom is real. Confirmation bias and complacency still exist. I’ve started to run out of times I’ve heard the phrase, “that’s why there’s two of us.” It is a team effort. The importance of a multi-pilot crew really starts to shine, and the idea of eventually having single pilot airline operations truly begins to sound asinine. Despite all the human shortfalls and emotions pilots are subject to, we are united in the goal to take our passengers from point a to b as safely as possible. The importance of week-1 private pilot concepts such as IMSAFE and PAVE have surely not disappeared. 

And that is not lost on me when I sit down in my seat, when I preflight, or when I double check something “just because.” The dedication should never stop just because you “made it.” ✈️
